<br>
I know personally that this frustrates me to no end.  Look at all the arguments about it.  I personally know that almost every high level guild has a severe disdain for the use of this.  I would say every but there is always an exception to the rule.<br>
<br>
I also know of three guilds of large size who expressly refuse to deal with anyone who uses the PST anacronym.  This may not be fair, but if you are using PST that right there is taking out a large part of the high end economy out of doing business with you.  <br>
<br>
I would like to know if anyone elses guilds have similar guidelines or such.  No its not a written policy of our guild, nor is it something that is enforced or anything, but if you ever saw the discussions we have had, or what has been said in guild, you would quickly understand.<br>
<br>
I read somewhere where someone said that instead of using PST that you may as well use DBSAI.... or Dont be stupid about it.   That there is my new motto.  When wanting to put PST at the end of your post, just remember DBSAI<br>
