<br>
Lets see.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, I am more than OK with them.  LFG is one that is generally accepted, and is OK.  so are ones like BRB and AFK<br>
<br>
Abbreviations in a tense combat situation are ok, too.  Im not gonna get mad if someone types ch plz in the middle of fighting something.<br>
<br>
BUT if you are asking someone to do you a favor (say asking a druid for a SoW), you dont say sow plz k thx, you say &quot;Can I get a spirit of the wolf, please&quot;<br>
<br>
Sure, it may seem petty.  But really, itll take a few more seconds out of your time...im sure you wont miss em.<br>
<br>
PST now, is a whole different beast -- It simply states something that is purely logical when someone is auctioning:<br>
<br>
&quot;Selling FBSS, 3kp.  PST&quot;<br>
<br>
What else am I going to do if you are auctioning something?  No need to tell me to send you a tell, if I want your item, I will send you a tell.  THATS why its so annoying, it gets to people on two counts -- the lack of necessity, and the fact that its an abbreviation in an un-necessary situation (especially if you use hot buttons for auctioning.)<br>
<br>
