<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/a.urmston1/siggy.bmp[/i"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umathas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#333333>(5/1/02 5:15:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=233.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Abbreviations.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I laugh at this too. People get upset with PST but things such as LFG, WTB WTS WTTF are accepted as just fine.<br>
<br>
What is the big deal with PST?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm going to guess here, but probably because &quot;PST&quot; is so freaking redundant it's laughable.  You could leave it off, and the sentence would mean the exact same thing.<br>
<br>
What ELSE would an intelligent person(note that I make this distinction) do, other than talk to you?  They certainly wouldn't stick their head out the window and shout at you.  They probably also wouldn't respond in /guildchat(unless you're in the same guild).  Sending a tell is the common sense thing to do.<br>
<br>
WTB/WTS/etc. are a bit more useful, though.  If I want to buy an Amulet of Necropotence, I'd be a moron to just type &quot;/auc Amulet of Necropotence&quot;.  I'd get about a hundred offers for it, when I really wanted to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> buy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> one.  &quot;/auc WTB:  Amulet of Necropotence&quot;, on the other hand, conveys my intent rather well, and I doubt I'd get many offers for something I don't have and want to buy.<br>
<br>
That said, PST doesn't bother me as much as it does some other people, just because I know there <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> are</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> idiots out there who <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> won't</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> send a /tell unless asked to, and would rather hold 5-minute conversations/arguments in an auction channel.  Yeah, I think PST is silly, and no, I'd never use it, but it doesn't irritate me <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> too</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> much. <p><hr width=335 align=LEFT><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123149">Mathas Oakheart</a> - 60th Hierophant, Bristlebane<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123576">Malkar Zauviir</a> - 54th Elementalist, Bristlebane<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pissed1vi2soe>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(5/1/02 6:23:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=233.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Abbreviations.</span><hr size=1> The level of the &quot;character&quot; using PST really has no bearing.  When you see a lvl 5 character (well twinked), saying PST you can see that it's there in the high end as well as the low end. <br>
<br>
If you LFG, it is implied that a group should send you a /tell if they wish to pick you up (no need for PST to make the obiouse more obviouse)<br>
<br>
If you /auction, it is implied that someone who wishes to buy/sell what you are /auctioning would send you a /tell (again PST is quite a bit redundant)<br>
<br>
Sit in EC and /ooc off, /shout off, watch the /auctions you will see /auction WTS uber high end gear 1, 2, 3, 4, etc for 20Kpp  PST.<br>
